Issues.Body:
### Steps to reproduce

Example steps (replace with your own):
1. Clone my repo at https://github.com/vovsemenv/playwright-ct-tailwind-problem
2. npm install
3. npm run test-ct
4. You should see the test is failed because styles from the tailwind doesnt applied.

However, if you do `npm run dev` or `npm run build && npm run preview` you can see tailwind classes works just fine.

### Expected behavior

I expect tailwind classes to appear and item with className="hidden" should be hidden

### Actual behavior

Classes doesn't applied and tests fail

### Additional context

```
import { test, expect } from "@playwright/experimental-ct-react";
import App from "./App";

test("should work", async ({ mount }) => {
  const component = await mount(<App />);
  const visible = component.locator('[data-test-id="visible"]');
  const hidden = component.locator('[data-test-id="hidden"]');
  await expect(visible).toBeVisible();
  await expect(hidden).not.toBeVisible();
});

```

```
function App() {
  return (
    <div>
      <div data-test-id="visible">visible</div>
      <div data-test-id="hidden" className="hidden">
        hidden
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;

```

